        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"><a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-r1-5-wildfires-ravaged" target="_blank">Wildfires ravaged</a> Southern California, and Los Angeles suffered immensely. The fires have killed at least 10 people and forced nearly 180,000 to evacuate from their homes. They have caused extensive property damage, affecting nearly all socioeconomic groups. Palisade fires have spread almost 20,000 acres, making it the most destructive in LA. Many residents in the Pacific Palisades report they have <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-r1-6-no-property-insurance" target="_blank">no property insurance</a> because insurance companies no longer provide coverage for this area. The economic loss from the fire damage is predicted to be <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-r1-7-up-to-150-billion" target="_blank">up to $150 billion</a>. Many have heavily criticized the LA mayor, Karen Bass, for <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-r1-8-handling-the-wildfire" target="_blank">handling the wildfire</a>. She left for Ghana on a diplomatic trip, which made many LA residents furious.</p>
