        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Monday, the first day of epiphany in the Catholic world, kicked off the first parade of the <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-r3-10-carnival-season" target="_blank">Carnival season</a>. This year's event was significant as the city was still recovering from a <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-r3-11-tragic-accident" target="_blank">tragic attack</a> five days earlier, in which 14 people were killed by a driver who later claimed to support ISIS. The parade organizers and participants emphasized themes of hope, joy, and resilience. However, many New Orleans residents are struggling with Mardi Gras this year from the trauma and wish there was <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-r3-12-more-accountability-and-action" target="_blank">more accountability and action</a> from the city than pushing themes such as resistance and hope.</p>
