            ">Did Tesla lay off U.S. workers to replace them with H-1B visa holders?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The issue of H-1B visas divided the MAGA camp, creating a <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-bq-13-mini-civil-war" target="_blank">mini-civil war</a> within the movement. In April 2024, <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-bq-14-tesla-laid-off" target="_blank">Tesla laid off</a> approximately 15,000 employees, primarily in Texas and California, and they were replaced by foreign workers using H-1B visas. In 2022, Tesla reportedly laid off 10% of its global workforce, including nearly 2,700 employees in Austin. The same year, the company requested over 2,000 H-1B visas to hire foreign workers. Musk argued that H-1B made America strong and that he would go to war against people who wanted to act against it.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Critics argue that the H-1B visa program may be misused to reduce labor costs, which could disadvantage US workers. Reports of <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-bq-16-80-hours-work-weeks" target="_blank">80-hour work weeks</a>, <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-bq-17-osha-violation" target="_blank">OSHA violations</a>, and efforts to <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-bq-18-prevent-unionization" target="_blank">prevent unionization</a> have heightened concerns about Tesla's worker treatment. Tesla CEO Elon Musk was a recipient of the H-1B program. He defends it by proposing reforms, such as raising the minimum wages for visa holders, to prioritize hiring domestic employees.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The division in the H-1B debate indicates more significant issues regarding immigration, labor practices, and corporate ethics. Stakeholders question whether H-1B visas are being used as intended and what reforms might ensure fair treatment for foreign and domestic workers.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
